<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-27T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-27T18:00:00-05:00" n="609" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d609">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">893.796/8–1248: Telegram</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)<note n="25" xml:id="d609fn25">Repeated to
                            the Consul at Tihwa as No. 32.</note>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-27T19:00:00-04:00">August 27,
                                1948—7 p. m.</date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>1239. Your 1489, Aug 12 and Tihwa’s 159, Aug 26 to Emb.<note n="26" xml:id="d609fn26">For the latter, see telegram No. 81, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> Providing Emb concurs Dept authorizes Emb inform
                        Tungling, FonOff director American Affairs, orally Dept gratified hear
                        ChiGovt has given USSR notice intention terminate agreement.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>